init_text:
What Are the Most Important Things Students Should Learn in School?

In your opinion, what are the most important things students should learn in school? What is the most important thing you have learned in school? How has this knowledge affected your life? How do you think it will help your success in the future?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the most important thing students should learn in school is how to be independent.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They should learn how to take care of themselves and not rely on others.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They should also learn how to be responsible for their actions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is important to be able to take care of yourself and not rely on others.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you can't do that, then you will have a hard time in life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You will have to rely on others for everything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You will have to ask for help and you won't be able to do anything on your own.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you are responsible for your actions, then you will be able to learn from your mistakes and not make the same mistake twice.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I learned how to be independent and responsible from my parents.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They taught me how to take care of myself and be responsible for my actions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: being able to do things for yourself is a better feeling.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I learned that being independent and responsible is the best way to live.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I learned that I can do anything I set my mind to.
